  "sections": {
    "overview": {
      "documented": true,
      "text": [
        "Gilgamesh is a swordsman who operates in close range and midrange. He draws a random weapon with every sword attack, which come with various effects. Weapon length, damage and EX Force generation all change depending on the weapon. Even Iai Strike (Bravery Break) is possible! All this is backed up by a well rounded air repertoire: Double Trouble is the quintessential fast poke |",
        "A fast attack that is used to occupy space, start offense and fill assist gauge.",
        "for safe plays, Electrocute controls space from afar and Whirlwind Slash closes gaps and starts various combos. Hurricane rounds out combos and catches off guard with its blindingly fast startup |",
        "The time it takes before an attack can do damage.",
        ".",
        "Gilgamesh’s strengths are characterized by his synergy with system mechanics and aerial attacks. He can fill assist and EX gauges at a steady rate with defensive play and Whirlwind Slash combos. While the reward varies with different weapons, Gilgamesh always benefits from EX; His damage potential skyrockets in EX mode thanks to his high base ATK, Octo Break and EX Burst, which is arguably the strongest in the game.",
        "Historically Gilgamesh has been ranked somewhere in mid tier. This has more to do with competitive representation than anything else. He’s not omnipotent though; His ground combat is comparatively slower and riskier. Random weapon draws could cause lots of damage or 1 damage per hit, with no way to guarantee an effect in most cases. Gilgamesh has very fast close-range attacks, but far slower, telegraphed midrange attacks. Gilgamesh picks between those two, and has nothing in between without sacrifices to his consistent air bravery loadout. If Gilgamesh is cornered, he has little upset potential outside of random weapon effects, high risk reads |",
        "A read is an educated guess informed by some knowledge or context in a match. An extremely risky move that works in this manner is considered a \"hard read\".",
        "and long-term defensive play. Overall Gilgamesh is generally well rounded in most important areas of the game, making him a competent character in competitive play."
      ],
      "tables": [
        {
          "caption": null,
          "rows": [
            [
              "Strengths",
              "Weaknesses"
            ],
            [
              "Aerial combat - Solo combos, quick poke, gap closer, lightning fast HP attack and ranged tools, Gilgamesh performs well in the most common area of the game.\nMid range anti-zoning - Electrocute is great at checking opponents at a distance, rewarding combos on hit.\nRandom weapons - Extraordinary effects such as instant bravery break, weapon length and increased EX generation are applied the moment Gilgamesh draws one of his 8 swords, which can turn the tides in his favor on a moment's notice.\nEX Mode - One of the strongest EX Bursts in the game, along with 8 wielded swords can exponentially increase Gilgamesh's reward on hit.\nFast faller - Whenever Gilgamesh air dodges, he is more difficult to hit out of it on average.",
              "Ground combat - Slow running speed, average HP attacks and lackluster bravery attacks pale in comparison to Gilgamesh's fundamentally solid aerial moves.\nRandom weapons - Gilgamesh cannot control which sword comes out, and may have to fight with suboptimal effects when he wants it the least.\nEX Revenge checkmates - With aerial Missile HP being slow on startup and the other single hit HPs being ground only, overcoming EX Revenge checkmates can be difficult."
            ]
          ]
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        "https://dissidia.wiki/Gilgamesh_(Dissidia_012)"
      ]
    },
